news.title: Protect land of petitioner, Telangana high court orders HYDRAA
news.para: The Telangana High Court intervened in a land dispute involving HYDRAA and two landowners, Jagal Reddy and Y Venkat Reddy, in Madhapur village. The court directed HYDRAA to remove its signboards from the disputed plots after landowners alleged illegal attempts to take possession and demolition of property without notice.

news.title: Transit-oriented development could transform Bengaluru traffic system
news.para: The state government will engage world-class private agencies through international bidding, moving away from relying solely on state-run institutions. Covering BBMP limits and beyond, over 500 sq km, the plan will utilise drone surveys, updated land-use maps, high-resolution images, and digital elevation models.

news.title: HC tells govt to issue circular to follow Madurai civic body model on property tax assessments
news.para: The Madras High Court, impressed by Madurai corporation's detailed action plan for property tax assessment, directed the state government to issue a circular. This circular instructs all corporations, municipalities, and town panchayats in Tamil Nadu to adopt Madurai's model. This action follows a PIL highlighting a significant property tax scam in Madurai, leading to substantial revenue loss.

news.title: Bihar to provide free land, interest subvention of up to ₹40 crore to investors under new policy: CM
news.para: Bihar government unveiled the 'Bihar Industrial Investment Promotion Package 2025' to boost industrial growth and create jobs. The policy offers free land allocation and interest subvention up to Rs 40 crore for investors. Units investing over Rs 100 crore or Fortune 500 companies can get free land.

news.title: Navsari civic body serves notices to 40 illegal under-construction sites
news.para: Navsari Municipal Corporation has initiated a crackdown on illegal construction. Notices were issued to 40 commercial and residential sites lacking valid permissions. The town planning department inspected 200 sites, demanding document submission within five days. Structures without approvals may face demolition. Ward-10 recorded the highest number of suspected illegal constructions.

news.title: Nazul land amnesty scheme extended; 5,000 leaseholders to benefit in Nagpur
news.para: The Maharashtra government has prolonged the special amnesty scheme for nazul lands in Nagpur and Amravati. This extension applies to lands leased for residential purposes. It is valid until July 31, 2026. The scheme allows conversion to freehold property at a reduced fee. Nagpur city has a significant number of nazul plots.

news.title: Chandigarh power company warns to pull the plug on 805 houses
news.para: Chandigarh Power Distribution Limited (CPDL) has issued disconnection notices to 805 homeowners for unauthorized constructions dangerously close to electric infrastructure across various sectors and colonies. These violations, including extended buildings and encroachments, breach safety regulations. Residents are instructed to remove these hazards to avoid electricity disconnection and legal action, ensuring public safety.

news.title: HYDRAA reclaims encroached land worth ₹100 crore in Hyderabad’s Jubilee Hills
news.para: HYDRAA reclaimed a 2,000 square yard plot in Jubilee Hills, valued at ₹100 crore, after over two decades of encroachment. The land, originally designated for community use by the Jubilee Hills Cooperative Housing Society, was illegally occupied by an individual running a nursery.

news.title: Noida: Over 120 families asked to vacate Janta flats after roof collapse
news.para: In Noida's Sector 31, approximately 130 families face displacement after a roof collapse exposed critical structural flaws in Janta and EWS flats. Years of seepage, neglect, and unauthorized modifications have rendered the buildings unsafe, prompting an evacuation advisory. Redevelopment plans offer long-term solutions, but residents grapple with immediate housing concerns and financial constraints.

news.title: Intra-district property registrations cross 60,000 in four months in Maharashtra
news.para: Maharashtra's intra-district property registration facility has surpassed 60,000 registrations since its launch on May 1st, allowing people to register property at any sub-registrar office within the same district. While residents are benefiting from the convenience, the inter-district registration is delayed due to technical and legal complexities.

news.title: Six districts to join Lucknow to form state capital region
news.para: Lucknow is poised for significant expansion with the launch of the State Capital Region (SCR) project, drawing inspiration from Delhi-NCR. The LDA has submitted a detailed report to the state government, encompassing six districts for integrated development.

news.title: ED arrests Sahiti Infratech's ex-director in ₹800 crore laundering case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) has arrested Sandu Purnachandra Rao, a former director at Sahiti Infratec Ventures, for allegedly defrauding homebuyers of ₹360 crore. Rao is accused of collecting over ₹800 crore through illegally launched projects and misappropriating ₹126 crore. He was remanded to 15-day judicial custody, joining B. Lakshminarayan, who was previously arrested in connection with the scam.

news.title: Chandigarh administration maintains status quo on group housing society property issues
news.para: Chandigarh administration will maintain the current regulations on property matters. This impacts group housing and cooperative societies. Issues include conversion charges and unearned increase. The administration has responded to the Ministry of Home Affairs. Need-based changes will not be allowed due to planning concerns. The decision affects thousands of flats in the city. GST on conversion fees is under consideration.

news.title: Full land digitisation to spur FDI in realty
news.para: India's ambitious goal to fully digitize land records by December is set to revolutionize the real estate sector, attracting significant foreign direct investment. Experts believe this move will streamline land acquisition, particularly for commercial and residential projects. With increased transparency and reduced disputes, the initiative aims to foster investor confidence and align India with global standards, potentially boosting FDI inflows.

news.title: No flat handover yet, Haryana RERA asks Agrante Realty to pay buyers for delay
news.para: Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority (HRera) has directed Agrante Realty to pay delayed possession charges to homebuyers of its Kavyam project in Sector 108, Gurugram. The developer failed to deliver possession by the due date, despite collecting nearly the entire sale consideration.

news.title: Welspun moves NCLT against Lavasa's top bidder Valor
news.para: The interlocutory application, filed through a Welspun subsidiary, also highlighted links between Valor's promoters and another defaulting debt-laden jeweller, links the plea claimed automatically disqualify the bidder to participate in any resolution process.

news.title: Property registration, MahaRERA portals to be linked to curb fraudulent deals
news.para: The Maharashtra registration department is set to integrate its property registration website with the MahaRERA portal to combat fraudulent property transactions. This integration will enable sub-registrars to verify RERA registration numbers in real-time, ensuring developers are registered before property registration.

news.title: Adani Group's proposal to buy debt-ridden Jaiprakash Associates gets CCI nod
news.para: The Competition Commission of India has approved Adani Group's bid for Jaiprakash Associates. This approval is for the ongoing insolvency proceeding. Other companies like Dalmia Bharat also received clearance. Jaiprakash Associates faced insolvency due to loan defaults. Creditors are claiming a significant amount. The company has real estate projects and cement plants. Suraksha Group previously acquired Jaypee Infratech.

news.title: REIT penetration in Indian office market can hit 30% by 2030: Colliers India
news.para: A Colliers India report projects India's office REIT penetration to reach 25-30% by 2030, up from the current 16%. Approximately 500 million sq ft of office assets are REIT-worthy, with significant potential in secondary business districts. Bengaluru, Hyderabad, and Delhi NCR hold the largest share of future REITable stock.

news.title: Hrithik Roshan rents sea-facing Juhu flat to partner Saba Azad at fraction of going rate
news.para: Hrithik Roshan has leased a sea-facing apartment in his Juhu property to his partner, Saba Azad, for a monthly rent of Rs 75,000. This is significantly lower than the prevailing market rates in the Mannat Apartments, where Roshan owns three floors. A comparable unit in the same building was leased for Rs 10 lakh per month earlier this year.
